    <section class="about-layout1 pb-130">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
                    <div class="heading-layout2">
                        <h3 class="heading__title mb-40">
                            <?= translator('Dear Patients and their relatives,', 'covid-19-bilgilendimre')?>
                        </h3>
                    </div><!-- /heading -->
                </div><!-- /.col-12 -->
            </div><!-- /.row -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div class="about__Text">
                        <p class="mb-30"> <?= translator('We would like to share with you the protective measures we have taken against the Corona (Covid-19) virus. Our measures have been determined in consultation with the expert authorities, in addition to the official instructions published by the Turkish Dental Association.', 'covid-19-bilgilendimre')?>
                            <br><br>
                            <?= translator('We have posted visual alerts (e.g. signs, posters) at the entrance and in strategic locations (e.g. waiting areas, elevators, cafeterias) to provide patients and dental clinic staff with instructions (in required languages) on hand hygiene, respiratory hygiene and cough etiquette.', 'covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            <br><br>
                            <?= translator('Instructions include how to use tissue paper/towels to cover the nose and mouth when coughing or sneezing, how to dispose of tissue/towels and contaminated materials in waste containers, and how and when to practice hand hygiene.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            <br><br>
                            <?= translator('At our clinic entrance, waiting rooms, and patient records, we have provided materials for respiratory hygiene and cough etiquette, including alcohol-based hand rub (ABHR) with 60-95% alcohol, tissue paper/towels, and non-woven bins and non-touch outlets for waste.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            <h5><?= translator('Evaluation of Patients at the Time of Appointment', 'covid-19-bilgilendirme')?></h5>
                        <br>
                        <?= translator('The pre-control staff asks patients about their health status, contact or travel history while making an appointment by phone.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        <br><br>
                        <?= translator('Our patient relations officer encourages the patient who enters the waiting area to use hand disinfectant first, the patient`s travel history is questioned and the temperature is measured. (Those who or their relatives were in the epidemic area 14 days ago and those who came from abroad constitute the risk group).','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        <br><br>
                        <?=translator('Relatives of adult patients who do not require care should not enter the waiting area. The waiting area is disinfected frequently and the environment should be ventilated. By keeping appointment intervals long, patient contact in waiting areas is minimized. We do not keep newspapers and magazines that will increase hand contact in the waiting areas during the pandemic.', 'covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        <br><br>
                        <?= translator('Patients who will be admitted to the dental unit area are first asked to read and sign the informed consent form. The Patient Anamnesis form is filled in by the physician in detail.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        <br><br><?= translator('The Patient Anamnesis form includes information about the epidemic region or travel abroad 2 weeks before, and information about influenza and fever in the recent past.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        <br><br><?= translator('Aseptic rules are followed during patient treatment. Before the patient sits in the unit, sterilized gauze pads, instruments, tools and equipment, and a cup in which the dirty waste will be placed next to the sterile instruments are prepared by packing.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>

                        <br><br><?=translator('Before the procedure, we give mouthwash containing 1% hydrogen peroxide or 0.2% povidone iodine to the patients.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?> <br><br>
                        <h5><?=translator('Corona Precautions of Pera Dental Polyclinic Health Personnel','covid-19-bilgilendirme   ')?>

                        </h5>
                        <?=translator('Hand hygiene is provided by the physician (hand rubbing or hand washing with alcohol-based hand antiseptic).','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?> <br><br>
                        <ul>
                            <li><?=translator('Hand hygiene is performed before and after all patient contact, including before hand contact with infectious material and before wearing gloves.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                            <li><?=translator('Hand hygiene after removing PPE is particularly important to remove pathogens that may have been transferred to bare hands during the removal process.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                            <li><strong><?=translator('Personal protective equipment;','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?></strong> <?=translator('The physician uses personal protective equipment such as gowns, masks, goggles, protective shields and gloves to protect the skin and mucous membranes during the removal process.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                            <li><?=translator('Hand hygiene is done by using 60-95% alcohol-based hand sanitizer or by washing hands with soap and water for at least 20 seconds.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <h5><?=translator('Mask;','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?></h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li><?=translator('A mask or face mask is put on before entering the patient room or care area.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                            <li><?=translator('Face masks, surgical masks, or N95 masks that offer a higher level of protection are used when performing an aerosol generating procedure or during the examination.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                            <li><?=translator('Disposable respirators and face masks are removed and discarded after leaving the patient`s room or care area and closing the door. Hand hygiene is practiced after discarding the mask or face mask.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <h5><?=translator('Eye Protection;','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </h5>
                        <ul>        
                            <li><?=translator('Eye protection (glasses or a disposable face shield that covers the front and sides of the face) is worn at the entrance to the patient room or care area.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <h5><?=translator('Glove;','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>

                        </h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li><?=translator('Clean gloves are worn at the entrance to the patient room or care area.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                            <li><?=translator('Torn or contaminated gloves are changed immediately.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                            <li><?=translator('When leaving the patient`s room or care area, gloves are removed and hand hygiene is applied immediately.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        </p>

                    </div>
                </div><!-- /.col-lg-6 -->
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div class="video-banner">
                        <img src="../assets/images/services/19.jpeg" alt="about">
                    </div><!-- /.video-banner -->
                    <p>
                    <h5><?=translator('Gown;','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>

                    </h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li><?=translator('At the entrance to the patient`s room or area, a clean isolation suit is worn.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <li><?=translator('The isolation gown is discarded in medical waste before leaving the patient`s room or care area.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <li><?=translator('After each use, disposable gowns are thrown. After each use, fabric aprons are washed according to the manufacturer`s instructions.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <li><?=translator('After the patient`s treatment is over, goggles/face protection and mask are removed and hand hygiene (rubbing or hand washing with alcohol-based hand antiseptic) is provided again. Treatments to be applied to patients in need of emergency treatment are carried out in an isolated and well-ventilated room.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <li><?=translator('Aerosol producing operations should be avoided if possible, and the cap and air water spray tips should be changed/sterilized at every patient change if necessary. To reduce the possibility of contamination, four-handed and rubber dams are employed, and high-speed wide-mouth aspirators are used for aerosol generating dental operations.Blood products and objects contaminated with them (gowns, glasses, gloves, masks, bonnets, doctor`s gowns, extracted teeth, saliva ejector, dressing material, etc.), sharps and needles: syringe needle, other sharps containing needles, scalpel, broken bulb etc. disposed of in the medical waste bin. The outer surfaces of the materials used, shields and goggles are disinfected with a rapid surface disinfectant.Non-sterile micromotor, cavitron, aerator, handpiece heads are not used for another patient. Micromotor, cavitron, aerators and handpiece are sent to sterilization to be sterilized if they are used. Dirty instruments are left in the dirty box containing enzymatic / disinfectant solution.Surfaces (unit table, hoses, headrest, reflector arm, etc.) are wiped from clean to dirty with a gauze cloth or disinfectant wipes wrung out with rapid surface disinfectant (the first wipe cleans the surface; then it is discarded; the surface is wiped again with a second wipe and waited for the effect of the disinfectant).','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <li><?=translator('The cuspidor is disinfected after it is washed and cleaned of dirt. (Chlorine tablet solution prepared with a chlorine content of 10000 ppm).','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <li><?=translator('After each procedure and after the patient leaves the room, the environment is ventilated following the cleaning and disinfection of the work area and its surroundings. (Door handles, drawer handles, tools and devices used in treatment, etc.)','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <li><?=translator('All auxiliary personnel in the clinic are ready with appropriate personal protective equipment during patient treatment.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <li><?=translator('Even during the simplest procedures in clinical settings, a clinical gown is always worn. Evaluation, separation, storage and transfer principles are followed in medical waste procedures.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>
                        </li>
                        <strong><?=translator('We wish you and your loved ones safe and healthy days.','covid-19-bilgilendirme')?>

                        </strong>
                    </ul>
                    </p>
                </div><!-- /.col-lg-6 -->
            </div><!-- /.row -->
        </div><!-- /.container -->
    </section><!-- /.About Layout 1 -->